() show newline
(This Memo specifies error handling and recovery for the Library of) show newline
(Cyberspace: how vaults detect, report, and recover from failures while) show newline
(maintaining integrity guarantees. Errors are first-class objects in the) show newline
(soup, enabling systematic analysis and automated recovery.) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(------------------------------------------------------------------------) show newline
(MOTIVATION) show newline
(------------------------------------------------------------------------) show newline
() show newline
(Distributed systems fail in creative ways:) show newline
() show newline
(  * Network partitions) show newline
(  * Vaults lose contact) show newline
(  * Storage corruption) show newline
(  * Bits flip, disks fail) show newline
(  * Byzantine faults) show newline
(  * Nodes lie or misbehave) show newline
(  * Resource exhaustion) show newline
(  * Out of memory, disk, connections) show newline
(  * Protocol violations) show newline
(  * Malformed messages, invalid state) show newline
() show newline
(These failure modes are not exceptional but routine; a distributed) show newline
(system that does not plan for them is planning to fail.) show newline
() show newline
(Recovery must be:) show newline
() show newline
(  * Deterministic) show newline
(  * Same error, same recovery) show newline
(  * Auditable) show newline
(  * Every error logged with context) show newline
(  * Automatic) show newline
(  * Self-healing where possible) show newline
(  * Graceful) show newline
(  * Degrade rather than crash) show newline
() show newline
(These requirements enable both automated recovery and post-mortem) show newline
(analysis; systems that crash silently cannot be trusted or debugged.) show newline
() show newline
